content.raw:
@dirk-thomas showed me some cool linking that they add to ROS jenkins jobs. For example in the left column of [this page](http://jenkins.ros.org/view/statuses/job/_pull_request-indigo-ros_comm/), you can see links to specific pull requests.

I believe these are generated by the [Description Setter Plugin](https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Description+Setter+Plugin).

Also, we could create optional parameters that allow the user to supply a link to the relevant pull request. I believe the jenkins bot could fill that in.
